Knee extensions target the muscles in the front of the thigh (quadriceps) and can help improve knee stability and function. Sit tall in a chair with feet flat on the floor. Straighten one leg out in front of you, lifting it off the ground. Hold briefly, then lower with control. Repeat for 10-12 reps on each leg.

• Sit tall in a chair with feet flat on the floor.
• Straighten one leg out in front of you, lifting it off the ground.
• Hold briefly, then lower with control.
• Repeat for 10-12 reps on each leg.
